  "title": "chore(examples): update links in next example",
  "body": "Next.js 13 changes how `<Link>` are rendered by having themselves an `<a>` tag, making implementations where `<a>` is in the userland code invalid.\r\n\r\nThis PR updates the references to `<Link>` in our examples to make them satisfy the new behaviour.\r\n\r\nSee: https://nextjs.org/docs/messages/invalid-new-link-with-extra-anchor",
